┌─────┬─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  I  │  INTRODUCTION                                                       │
└─────┴─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
                           
        Your mission is to destroy many ennemy bases on the path of your
bomber, a B-29. The first B-29s were created back in 1943 and have been
used a lot by the american army. The B-29 is equipped with one 20mm cannon,
a double .50mm machine gun and 22,000 lbs of bombs. It has been modified
a little for this game!
        
        Many obstacles are on your path such as tanks, helicopters,
warships and more! Will you be able to keep up?

        Bomber is a game which has many features that makes it a superior
quality game, such as:
        
■ Stunning 256 color VGA graphics
■ Musical theme and digitized sound effets on a Sound Blaster or compatible
■ Many unique levels
        
        I hope that you'll enjoy bomber. Many hours of work have been put in
this game, therefore I ask you to consider registering Bomber if you like it.
        
The author, Patrick Pichѓ
        
 
┌─────┬─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ II  │  SYSTEM REQUIREMENTS                                                │
└─────┴─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
                              
        Bomber should work on any 386 or more with at least 400K of free
conventional memory, but if you want the game to take full advantage of all
its features and be fast enough, a 33Mhz or more processor is recommended.
This game uses special 386 instructions, and thus will NOT work a 286
machines, sorry. The game supports the Sound Blaster for the playback
of music and digitized sound effects.

        The first time you run BOMBER, you'll be asked to configure the
game to fit your needs. You have to choose between english or french,
sound or no sound, and in which special playing mode you want to play.
If you want to change the configuration after that, you can run
SETUP.BAT or simply BOMBER with any argument.


 Bomber 2.2 - The REAL arcade game!                                   Page 3
┌─────┬─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ III │  THE GAME                                                           │
└─────┴─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

        Bomber is very easy to start from DOS, you only have to type 
BOMBER.EXE and it will automatically detect the type of sound card installed
in your system. The keys used in the game are the following:
        
        Direction of your bomber: Cursor keys
        Fire bullets            : CTRL
        Fire bombs              : ALT
        Quit the game           : ESC
        Pause                   : Space bar

        That's it! Now, try to destroy the 3 bases of the game! You'll start
in a forest and the ennemy base will be at the end at about 200Km (120 
miles). After that, other scenarios will be presented to you, it's up to you 
to discover them! Note that the red cross is your aim and it's at its 
position on the ground that your bombs will blow up.

        You can eliminate gound ennemies with your bombs and helicopters with
your machine guns. There's no ammo limit, this game has been created for you
to let go your frustrations and not to frustrate you more!!! Let go your
destructive instinct and enjoy! You'll start with three lives and you gain one
more for every 10,000 points scored.


